3. The aforesaid Deputy Engineer (Electrical) shall assume charge of the new post forthwith and submit his report to the Government without delay. The aforesaid engineers shall take care to join the place of transfer by the transferred engineers within the period of appointment as provided in the Maharashtra Civil Services (Period of assumption, non-acceptance of service and payments during periods of suspension, dismissal and removal from service) Rules, 1981, otherwise, if they do not join the post of transfer during the period of assumption of office, their absence shall be deemed to be non-deceasing days. Their attention is also being drawn to Rule 23 of the Maharashtra Civil Services (Conduct) Rules 1979. Taking note of the provisions of this rule, he
They are liable for disciplinary action if they submit an application of any nature for transfer to the post.

4. The Controlling Authorities concerned are informed that they should immediately inform the Government of the date of demitting office and the date of assumption of office by the demitting officers. the concerned officer during the prescribed period.

In case of non-attendance at the place of transfer, the same should be communicated to the Government immediately so that disciplinary action can be taken against the concerned expeditiously. As per Rule 30 (c) of the MNS (Leave) Rules, 1981, leave applications of transferred officers should not be accepted / sanctioned.
